5.  Senior program analyst (national, 18 person-months). A senior program analyst, based 
at Asian Development Bank (ADB) headquarters, should have experience working with South 
and Southeast Asian countries. The analyst will 
(i)  support the preparation of policy briefs, and other substantive work; 
(ii)  support logistics requirements and assignments, support the technical assistance 
(TA) activities; and arrange conferences, workshops, and meetings for the TA;  
(iii)  help  ADB  staff  with  TA  administration,  including  budget  preparation  and 
liquidation of all individual activities under the TA;  
(iv)  prepare and maintain a comprehensive and orderly filing system for the TA, and 
update files regularly;  
(v)  help ensure the smooth flow of documents and communications related to TA 
implementation;  
(vi)  assist the ADB TA team in managing the implementation database;  
(vii)  help draft routine communications; and  
(viii)  participate in ADB missions, conferences, workshops, seminars, and meetings as 
required. 

6.  Web design specialist (national, 18 person-months). A web design specialist will be 
based in Dhaka to: 
(i)  assist in developing the BIMSTEC website, 
(ii)  provide regular website maintenance, and 
(iii)  provide training on web maintenance for the BIMSTEC Secretariat.
